<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15990</anchor> <rss>jms-009S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Project</taxon> <addr>jms-009S</addr>  <route>jms-009S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="mikeshulman.xml" type="local">Michael Shulman</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Strong impredicative encodings</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15991</anchor> <rss>jms-009T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Log</taxon> <addr>jms-009T</addr>  <route>jms-009T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="2023-09-29.xml" type="local" title="2023-09-29">2023-09-29</link> / <link href="jms-009S.xml" type="local" title="Strong impredicative encodings">strong impredicative encodings</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p><link href="mikeshulman.xml" type="local" title="Michael Shulman">Michael Shulman</link> has sent me a potential proof of <link href="jms-003M.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-idempotent in a wild category">quasi-idempotence</link> for the generic element of a <link href="jms-003H.xml" type="local" title="Wild semicoherent natural transformations">semicoherent cone</link>. This relies on a “fattened” definition of semicoherence in the wild-categorical setting, similar to Mike’s <link href="jms-003W.xml" type="local" title="Semicoherence structure">fattened version</link> in the special case of subuniverses. <link href="mikeshulman.xml" type="local" title="Michael Shulman">Mike</link> points out that the condition, when specialized for cones over the identity functor, is much simpler than the general case. I am thinking that I might see if it is possible to formalize it in <link href="typetopology.xml" type="local" title="TypeTopology">TypeTopology</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15992</anchor> <rss>2023-09-27.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-09-27</addr>  <route>2023-09-27.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-09-27</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>I finished my pass through <link href="sterling-2023-grothendieck.xml" type="local" title="Towards a geometry for syntax">towards a geometry for syntax</link> and submitted the revision to the arXiv.</p><p>Today I added an experimental <code>\iftex</code> command to <link href="jms-009Q.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.5 [unreleased]">Forester 2.5 [unreleased]</link> in response to <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link>’s post to the mailing list.</p><p>I started to resume my <link href="jms-0036.xml" type="local" title="Reflectivity of impredicative subuniverses">work</link> on <link href="jms-009S.xml" type="local" title="Strong impredicative encodings">strong impredicative encodings</link> in intensional type theory with <link href="mikeshulman.xml" type="local" title="Michael Shulman">Michael Shulman</link> in terms of <link href="jms-003A.xml" type="local" title="Wild category theory">wild category theory</link>. I ended up getting totally snowed under coherences and asked <link href="mikeshulman.xml" type="local" title="Michael Shulman">Michael Shulman</link> for help.</p><p>My <link href="jms-008K.xml" type="local" title="New spaces for denotational semantics">new spaces for denotational semantics</link> grant was awarded by <link href="afosr.xml" type="local" title="United States Air Force Office of Scientific Research">United States Air Force Office of Scientific Research</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>